{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"79d7ccd6-2ff5-4630-ae3b-1efaffc3fa74","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility layer by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk **3.8**, the SDK began shipping with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (the new runner) as the default. However, it still included the VSTest bridge adapter so `vstest.console` continued to work.\n\nIn **MSTest.Sdk 4.x**, the VSTest bridge adapter is **no longer included by default**. This means `vstest.console` (and `dotnet test` in VSTest mode) can't discover or run your tests.\n\n### You have two options:\n\n**Option A — Switch your CI to the new runner (recommended):**\n```bash\n# Run tests directly via the built-in test runner\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj\n# or\ndotnet test  # uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default with SDK 4.x\n```\n\n**Option B — Re-enable the VSTest bridge** if you must keep `vstest.console`:\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n</PropertyGroup>\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n**Option A** is the recommended path forward since VSTest compatibility is being phased out.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f450b218-2f8a-43c9-96dd-0f9f101dfc53","outputTokens":338,"requestId":"0C03:278C9F:6615B3E:6F92E74:69F02444"},"id":"eeeca6e8-20e6-4363-9145-8e0a43d6226d","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:06:54.312Z","parentId":"e5cdd683-013d-4dc2-b337-3f78d04605d3"}
